commit.message: Use GitHub Actions for CI

Remove Travis-CI.org config

Travis-CI.org shutdown building projects. Alternatives are either using
Travis-CI.com or using GitHub Actions which is better integrated and
more clear that it's free for all repositories.
preferences: no need to apply toolbar preferences after preferences dialog anymore
preferences: remove the now empty frame for toolbar options
preferences: remove option for toolbar style, always use the “both” style (icon and text)
preferences: remove option for toolbar tooltips, always enable them
preferences: remove gtkrc option
Prepare for GTK3
Use more readable syntax to set struct values

Ignore -Wdeprecated-declarations on GTK2

(GTK2 itself uses deprecated declarations)
Remove useless GTK includes
Fix depreciation warnings with newer glib
Replace ouned.de JK2 master with jk2mv.org (same ip, official domain)

Compiles with either minizip 1 or 2 (issue #223)

Compiled binary must be linked to the same version it was compiled
with
Minizip 2.x API compatibility
Fix duplicate global variable definitions
masters: add hambloch.com kingpin master server

stat: filter http server list and fix a crash

- filter http server list for bad character
- fix a crash related to string allocation

Merge pull request #217 from aufau/faufixes

Few minor fixes and improvements
